Privacy Policy
Last updated: 10 December, 2024

This privacy policy governs your use of the Treasure Hunter: Gold & Metal Detector application (hereafter referred to as "the App"). We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring a secure user experience.

1. Data Collection
We do not collect any personal or non-personal information from users. The App is designed to function without requiring any personally identifiable information (PII).

2. Third-Party Services
The App uses Google AdMob for advertising purposes. AdMob may collect certain information to display personalized ads, such as device information, location, and usage data. This information is collected and processed by AdMob, and we do not have access to it.

For more information on how AdMob handles your data, please review Google's Privacy Policy.

3. Permissions
The App may request the following permissions:

Location: To provide relevant features for detecting gold or metal nearby. This permission is used solely for the app's functionality and not for any data collection purposes.
4. Data Usage
As stated, we do not collect or store any data from users. Any data collected through third-party services like AdMob is used solely for advertising purposes as outlined in their respective privacy policies.

5. Data Sharing
We do not share, sell, or rent any personal information, as we do not collect it. However, third-party services like AdMob may share data in accordance with their privacy policies.

6. Security
Although we do not collect any personal data, we take reasonable measures to protect the integrity of the App and ensure a safe user experience.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
The App is not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child under 13, please contact us so we can address the issue.

8. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We recommend reviewing this policy periodically.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy, feel free to contact us at betapixel92@gmail.com.
